      "content": "thanks. the food and music ideas are helpful. i guess i'm also trying to get a sense of the tension that can happen in these settings. like, when there's conflict, does it usually come from specific things? for example, is there a stereotype about these families being really loud or maybe having a certain kind of struggle or \"street\" element that's common in these kinds of dramas? i just want to know what the typical tropes or \"realities\" are so i can decide whether to use them or subvert them.",
